name: Rock the Joint
comments: Lead guitarist, Danny Cedrone, performed one of the most memorable guitar solos in rock history on this recording. He repeated it note for note in 1954 when he recorded "Rock Around the Clock" with Bill Haley. The song was re-recorded on July 15, 1957 as by Bill Haley and His Comets for Rock the Joint .

comments: David Bowie played piano on this version. Noone replaced Bowie's line "The Earth is a bitch" with "The Earth is a beast", in a performance that NME editors Roy Carr and Charles Shaar Murray opined to be "one of rock and roll's most outstanding examples of a singer failing to achieve any degree of empathy whatsoever with the mood and content of a lyric". The song was titled "Oh You Pretty Thing" on its first pressing. Later repressings added the missing "s".
